go_data.justification: TRIP overexpression enhanced TNF-mediated cell death in HeLa cells.
TNF-induced NF-kappaB activation was inhibited by TRIP overexpression.

Members of the tumor necrosis factor receptor (TNFR) superfamily elicit a wide range of biological effects including differentiation, proliferation, activation, or cell death through their interaction with the TNF receptor-associated factor (TRAF) family.
TNF is a secreted protein that interacts with the TNF receptor on the cell surface.
